<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/94bc88ea104571db3bce2e9cf472dbe9.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 6 and c = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.3</li><li>48.6</li><li>41.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}^{{2}}={6}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}={36}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}-{36}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{28}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{28}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.2915026221292}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.3}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{6}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{48.590377890729}\approx{48.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{6}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{41.409622109271}\approx{41.4}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

